transcript.text: Hello, welcome to the On Print Shop version 11.0 feature tutorial series.
In today's video, we are introducing the Create Template from Indesign feature that streamlines template creation for administrators.
With the version 11.0 release, administrators can now initiate Indesign template creation directly from the Template listing page.
During template creation, they will have the option to export the IDML file from the Indesign tool and seamlessly import it into the admin panel.
So let's see how it's done.
Log into your OPS admin panel from the left navigation panel, go to the Templates section and click on the Product Templates.
From the Template listing page.
You will find a new button named Create from Indesign at the top right corner of the screen.
Click on the Create from Indesign button and it will take you to the Add Template page where you can create customizable or non customizable templates as per the standard process.
Once you have filled in all the details, click on Save and Continue.
You will land on the Edit Design tab where you need to upload your exported IDML file using the Upload Indesign File button.
As soon as you import the file, new sections for uploading fonts and images will appear.
You have the option to upload all the asset files as a zip file or you can upload them individually from the respective sections.
After you have uploaded all the required files, click on Save and Continue.
The design template will open in the Designer Studio for you to verify and modify the template as per your requirements.
As you click on Continue, the template will be saved and will appear in the template listing.
Similar to other templates, you can add additional preview images, manage template properties, edit the field order, edit the design, create a new version, or even delete the template here.
Clicking on the Edit from Indesign will take you to the Edit Design tab where you can import the IDML file or other assets.
That's it.
With our new Indesign file support, the admin can save their time in template creations.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chat on onprintshop.com.
Thanks for tuning in.
Thanks for watching this video.
